# Vercel Speed Insights Installation Report

## Summary
Successfully installed and configured Vercel Speed Insights for this React + Vite portfolio project.

## Implementation Details

### 1. Documentation Fetched
- Retrieved latest installation instructions from: https://vercel.com/docs/speed-insights/quickstart
- Confirmed framework-specific instructions for React/Vite projects

### 2. Package Installation
- Installed `@vercel/speed-insights` version 2.0.0 using npm
- Package added to dependencies in package.json
- Lock file (package-lock.json) updated with new dependencies

### 3. Code Changes

**Modified Files:**
- `src/App.jsx` - Added Speed Insights integration

**Changes Made:**
1. Added import statement: `import { SpeedInsights } from '@vercel/speed-insights/react';`
2. Added `<SpeedInsights />` component in the App return statement, positioned alongside the existing `<Analytics />` component

### 4. Testing & Verification
✅ Lint check passed - No ESLint errors
✅ Build successful - Project compiles without errors
✅ Bundle size: 311.05 kB (gzipped: 98.42 kB)

## Next Steps for Deployment
Once deployed to Vercel:
1. Enable Speed Insights in the Vercel Dashboard (Project Settings → Speed Insights)
2. Deploy the changes using `vercel deploy`
3. Verify installation by checking for `/<unique-path>/script.js` in the page's head tag
4. Monitor performance metrics in the Speed Insights dashboard

## Files Updated
- package.json - Added @vercel/speed-insights dependency
- package-lock.json - Updated with new package dependencies
- src/App.jsx - Integrated SpeedInsights component

## Notes
- Speed Insights component follows the same pattern as the existing Analytics component
- Positioned at the root level to track all pages
- Implementation follows official Vercel documentation for React projects
- Data collection will begin automatically upon deployment to Vercel
